2026-05-13 02:47:04,215 - ra_aid.ra_aid.__main__ - DEBUG - Recorded CLI input: Fix a bug in router.py in this repository.

The bug: When classify_intent() receives an uppercase intent string from the LLM (e.g., "CODE" instead of "code"), the intent lookup fails because INTENT_CATEGORIES keys are all lowercase. The code currently does:

    intent = classification.get("intent", "chat")
    plan = INTENT_CATEGORIES.get(intent, INTENT_CATEGORIES["chat"])

This means "CODE" is not found in INTENT_CATEGORIES and falls back to "chat" instead of "code".

The fix: Normalize the intent to lowercase before lookup:

    intent = classification.get("intent", "chat").lower()

Validation:
1. Run: python3 -m pytest tests/test_router_intent_lookup.py -v
2. All 3 tests must pass (including test_uppercase_intent_normalization)
3. Run: python3 -m py_compile router.py
4. No phantom changes to unrelated files

